  "body": "## Problem\n\nOne of our ambassadors found that the V1 RC9 doesn't show Spanish well on Android devices. It partially shows Spanish so I guess it uses other Spanish translations(`es.json` or `es_ar.json` or `es_mx.json`) instead. The V1 RC9 Spanish works well on iOS so Android uses different locale systems from iOS.\n\n## Suggestion\n\nI think we should  remove `es_ar.json(Argentina)` and `es_mx.json(Mexico)` like what we are doing for Chinese(`zh.json`). Also, `es.json` should have the same translations as `es_419.json` temporarily.\n\nAn ambassador from Colombia said the Latin American Spanish is similar to Spanish in Spain so there is almost no problem with using the current `es_419` for all the Spanish translations (although it is not ideal).\n\nIf we cannot make any changes until V1 now, I think it is safer to [remove](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/f9c15be1d41059f68fc597d7f3ee7be6dae5e0e3/prod/status_im/i18n_resources.cljs#L8) Spanish(doesn't work on Android) and Russian(not reviewed) until V1.1.\n\n## Notes\n\nThe list of languages that are ready for V1 is:\n- Korean\n- Chinese\n- Arabic\n- Italian\n\nLanguages that need more reviews:\n- Spanish (Android X)\n- French (Not merged yet)\n- Russian (Needs more review)\n\nI think we should prune some languages at [18n_resources](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/f9c15be1d41059f68fc597d7f3ee7be6dae5e0e3/prod/status_im/i18n_resources.cljs#L8) which are not ready yet.\n\nWDYT?",
